text: Ajda is an Arabic and Turkish surname and given name, and a Slovene word for buckwheat, infrequently also used as a female given name. It may refer to: * Ajda Novak, Slovenian slalom canoeist * Ajda Pekkan (born 1946), also known as Süperstar, Turkish pop singer and actress * Masruq ibn al-Ajda' (died 682), tabi'i, jurist and muĥaddith == See also == * == References == Category:Arabic-language surnames Category:Arabic feminine given names Category:Turkish feminine given names
title: Ajda
